.LONG TERM...
Issued at 105 AM PDT Tue Jul 21 2026
(Wednesday through Monday)

As mentioned in the short term discussion, elevated pw will remain
from the surface to the lower levels tonight. This will carry over
through Wednesday. This is tropical moisture that`ll keep surface
dewpoint temperatures in the upper 50s/60s Wednesday. Dewpoints in
this range will make it feel muggy Wednesday while the mid to upper
levels will be drier. If low clouds return by early Wednesday, patchy
light measurable drizzle may develop in the tropical air mass. Weak
cool air advection, onshore winds and gentle upsloping may help with
the development of patchy drizzle.

Daytime onshore breezes return mid to late week. It`ll otherwise
be dry, warm to hot inland and coolest at the coast and bays later
in the week. The high pressure system over the interior west will
gradually shift southward then slowly move to the Four Corners by
the weekend.

