.AVIATION...
(12Z TAFS)
Issued at 420 AM PDT Tue Jul 21 2026

Currently VFR with mid-level clouds and elevated rain showers
streaming in from the south. Both of these features are contributing
to VFR by mixing out the marine layer and limiting radiational
cooling. As such, high confidence in VFR through the afternoon. The
marine layer is expected to reform tonight around 1,000 feet which
would bring ceilings on the cusp of IFR/MVFR to bayshore and coastal
terminals with lower confidence farther inland. This may be generous
given the over performance of guidance and models currently, it`ll
all depend on if mid-level clouds can clear overnight. Elevated rain
showers moving in from the south will bring virga to the region.
Diurnal winds will prevail.

Vicinity of SFO...Currently VFR with westerly flow. Moderate to high
confidence on VFR prevailing through the TAF period. If a ceiling
were to develop tomorrow night, it`ll likely be MVFR.

SFO Bridge Approach...Similar to SFO.

Monterey Bay Terminals...Currently VFR and calm at MRY and VFR with
drainage flow at SNS. High confidence in VFR through the morning
with low to moderate confidence on ceilings on the cusp of IFR/MVFR
returning tonight.

