.MARINE...
(Today through Sunday)
Issued at 420 AM PDT Tue Jul 21 2026

Isolated elevated rain showers may result in erratic and gusty
winds capable of generating steep seas today. Light  northwesterly
breezes are expected today, backing to become  southerly tomorrow.
Hazardous conditions for small craft may return as early as
Thursday as northwesterly breezes return and  increase to become
moderate to fresh through Saturday. Moderate  southwesterly swell
from tropical cyclone activity in the Eastern Pacific will bring
mixed seas and potentially hazardous conditions through the
weekend.

